title: Permutations II
description:
Permutations II

Leetcode 47. Permutations II

You are given an array `nums`, that might contain duplicates , return all possible unique permutations in **any order**.

Examples:

  • Input: nums = [1,1,2]

    Output: [
    [1,1,2],
    [1,2,1],
    [2,1,1]
    ]
  • Input: nums= [2,2]

    Output: [[2,2]]

Constraints:

  • `1 <= nums.length <= 8`
  • `-10 <= nums[i] <= 10`
